4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT REVISING THE DEFINITION OF "SMOKING" IN THE CLEAN
5 INDOOR AIR ACT; PROVIDING A DEFINITION OF "ELECTRONIC SMOKING DEVICE"; AMENDING
6 SECTION 50-40-103, MCA; AND PROVIDING AN IMMEDIATE EFFECTIVE DATE.”
7
8 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
9
10 Section 1. Section 50-40-103, MCA, is amended to read:
11 "50-40-103. Definitions. As used in this part, the following definitions apply:
12 (1) "Bar" means an establishment with a license issued pursuant to Title 16, chapter 4, that is
13 devoted to serving alcoholic beverages for consumption by guests or patrons on the premises and in which the
14 serving of food is only incidental to the service of alcoholic beverages or gambling operations. The term
15 includes but is not limited to taverns, night clubs, cocktail lounges, and casinos.
16 (2) "Department" means the department of public health and human services provided for in 2-15-
17 2201.
18 (3) "Electronic smoking device" means a product containing or delivering nicotine or another
19 substance intended for human consumption that can be used by a person in any manner for the purpose of
20 inhaling vapor or aerosol from the product. The term includes a device manufactured, distributed, marketed, or
21 sold as an e-cigarette, e-cigar, e-pipe, e-hookah, dab rig, or vape pen, or under any other product name or
22 descriptor.
23 (3) (4) "Enclosed public place" means an indoor area, room, or vehicle that the general public is
24 allowed to enter or that serves as a place of work, including but not limited to the following:
25 (a) restaurants;
26 (b) stores;
27 (c) public and private office buildings and offices, including all office buildings and offices of
28 political subdivisions, as provided for in 50-40-201, and state government;
