1 (d) trains, buses, and other forms of public transportation;
2 (e) health care facilities;
3 (f) auditoriums, arenas, and assembly facilities;
4 (g) meeting rooms open to the public;
5 (h) bars;
6 (i) community college facilities;
7 (j) facilities of the Montana university system; and
8 (k) public schools, as provided for in 20-1-220 and 50-40-104.
9 (4) (5) "Establishment" means an enterprise under one roof that serves the public and for which a
10 single person, agency, corporation, or legal entity is responsible.
11 (5) (6) "Incidental to the service of alcoholic beverages or gambling operations" means that at least
12 60% of the business's annual gross income comes from the sale of alcoholic beverages or gambling receipts,
13 or both.
14 (6) (7) "Person" means an individual, partnership, corporation, association, political subdivision, or
15 other entity.
16 (7) (8) "Place of work" means an enclosed room where one or more individuals work.
17 (8) (9) (a) "Smoking" or "to smoke" includes means the act of:
18 (i) lighting, smoking, or carrying a lighted cigar, cigarette, pipe, or any smokable product, and
19 includes including the use of marijuana; or
20 (ii) inhaling, exhaling, burning, or carrying a lighted or heated cigar, cigarette, pipe, hookah, or any
21 other lighted or heated tobacco or plant product, whether natural or synthetic, intended for inhalation, including
22 marijuana or cannabis, in any manner or any form.
23 (b) The term includes the use of an electronic smoking device that creates an aerosol or vapor, in
24 any manner or in any form, or the use of any oral smoking device for the purpose of circumventing the
25 prohibition of smoking in Title 50, chapter 40, part 1."
26
27 NEW SECTION. Section 2. Effective date. [This act] is effective on passage and approval.
